1
00:01:40,727 --> 00:01:42,497
There was me.

2
00:01:42,897 --> 00:01:45,627
That is, Alex,
and my three droogs.

3
00:01:45,907 --> 00:01:49,536
That is, Pete, Georgie and Dim.

4
00:01:49,976 --> 00:01:53,496
And we sat in the Korova Milk Bar,
trying to make up our rassoodocks...

5
00:01:53,746 --> 00:01:56,006
what to do with the evening.

6
00:01:57,716 --> 00:02:00,806
The Korova Milk Bar sold milk plus.

7
00:02:01,056 --> 00:02:04,715
Milk plus vellocet or
synthemesc or drencrom...

8
00:02:04,925 --> 00:02:06,915
which is what we were drinking.

9
00:02:07,495 --> 00:02:08,885
This would sharpen you up

10
00:02:09,095 --> 00:02:13,055
and make you ready for a bit
of the old ultra-violence.

11
00:02:17,395 --> 00:02:20,894
In Dublin's fair city

12
00:02:21,574 --> 00:02:25,704
Where the girls are so pretty

13
00:02:26,774 --> 00:02:29,834
I first set my eyes

14
00:02:30,914 --> 00:02:34,503
On sweet Molly Malone

15
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:40,283
As she wheeled her wheelbarrow

16
00:02:40,553 --> 00:02:44,923
Through streets broad and narrow

17
00:02:45,223 --> 00:02:49,633
Crying, "Cockles and mussels"

18
00:02:50,592 --> 00:02:52,692
One thing I could never stand

19
00:02:52,902 --> 00:02:55,302
was to see a filthy,
dirty old drunkie

20
00:02:55,572 --> 00:02:58,232
howling away at the
filthy songs of his fathers

21
00:02:58,542 --> 00:03:00,802
and going "blerp blerp"
in between

22
00:03:01,042 --> 00:03:05,301
as it might be a filthy old
orchestra in his stinking guts.

23
00:03:05,581 --> 00:03:09,211
I could never stand to see anyone
like that, whatever his age.

24
00:03:09,411 --> 00:03:12,581
But more especially when he
was real old, like this one was.

25
00:03:20,221 --> 00:03:24,250
Can you spare some cutter,
me brothers?

26
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:32,490
Go on! Do me in, you bastard cowards!
I don't want to live anyway.

27
00:03:32,770 --> 00:03:35,600
Not in a stinking world
like this.

28
00:03:38,339 --> 00:03:41,509
And what's so stinking about it?

29
00:03:41,749 --> 00:03:46,009
It's a stinking world because
there's no law and order anymore!

30
00:03:46,279 --> 00:03:49,339
It stinks because it lets
the young get onto the old

31
00:03:49,619 --> 00:03:51,648
like you done!

32
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:56,758
It's no world
for an old man any longer.

33
00:03:57,328 --> 00:04:00,758
What kind of a world is it
at all?

34
00:04:00,998 --> 00:04:02,858
Men on the moon.

35
00:04:03,168 --> 00:04:05,658
Men spinning around the earth.

36
00:04:05,868 --> 00:04:08,927
And there's not no
attention paid

37
00:04:09,137 --> 00:04:12,697
to earthly
law and order no more.

38
00:04:13,037 --> 00:04:15,637
Oh, dear land

39
00:04:16,047 --> 00:04:18,337
I fought for thee

40
00:04:53,644 --> 00:04:57,374
It was at the derelict casino
that we came across Billy-boy

41
00:04:57,654 --> 00:04:59,674
and his four droogs.

42
00:05:00,014 --> 00:05:02,414
They were about to perform
a little of the old

43
00:05:02,724 --> 00:05:06,654
in-out, in-out on a weepy
young devotchka they had there.

44
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:59,640
Well, if it isn't fat, stinking

45
00:05:59,940 --> 00:06:04,210
billy goat
Billy-boy in poison.

46
00:06:05,050 --> 00:06:06,640
How are thou

47
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:10,749
thou globby bottle of cheap,
stinking chip-oil?

48
00:06:12,449 --> 00:06:15,049
Come and get one in the yarbles

49
00:06:15,289 --> 00:06:17,149
if you have any yarbles

50
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:20,419
you eunuch jelly, thou.

51
00:06:23,899 --> 00:06:25,558
Let's get them, boys!

52
00:07:23,655 --> 00:07:25,015
The police!

53
00:07:25,655 --> 00:07:27,284
Come on. Let's go!

54
00:07:48,213 --> 00:07:52,803
The Durango 95 purred away
real horror show.

55
00:07:53,013 --> 00:07:57,242
A nice, warm vibratey feeling
all through your guttiwuts.

56
00:07:57,512 --> 00:08:00,682
Soon it was trees and dark,
my brothers

57
00:08:00,922 --> 00:08:03,482
with real country dark.

58
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:43,519
We fillied around with other
travelers of the night

59
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:46,129
playing Hogs of the Road.

60
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:48,349
Then we headed west.

61
00:08:48,599 --> 00:08:52,299
What we were after now
was the old surprise visit.

62
00:08:52,539 --> 00:08:53,759
That was a real kick

63
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:58,468
and good for laughs and
lashing of the old ultra-violent.

64
00:09:46,915 --> 00:09:48,915
Who on earth could that be?

65
00:09:57,995 --> 00:09:59,584
I'll go and see.

66
00:10:10,374 --> 00:10:12,004
Yes, who is it?

67
00:10:12,274 --> 00:10:16,273
Excuse me, can you please help?
There's been a terrible accident!

68
00:10:17,343 --> 00:10:21,613
My friend's bleeding to death!
Can I please use your telephone?

69
00:10:21,853 --> 00:10:25,153
We don't have a telephone.
You'll have to go somewhere else.

70
00:10:25,353 --> 00:10:28,053
But, missus, it's a matter
of life and death!

71
00:10:28,323 --> 00:10:29,623
Who is it, dear?

72
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:32,452
A young man.
He says there's been an accident.

73
00:10:32,662 --> 00:10:35,322
He wants to use the telephone.

74
00:10:36,362 --> 00:10:38,802
I suppose you better let him in.

75
00:10:39,832 --> 00:10:41,702
Wait a minute, will you?

76
00:10:43,872 --> 00:10:47,141
I'm sorry, but we don't usually
let strangers in

77
00:10:59,221 --> 00:11:01,080
What do you want from me?

78
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:07,660
Pete, check the rest
of the house. Dim

79
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,730
I'm singing in the rain

80
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:17,699
Just singing in the rain

81
00:11:18,539 --> 00:11:20,369
What a glorious feeling

82
00:11:21,239 --> 00:11:22,729
I'm happy again

83
00:11:24,109 --> 00:11:25,939
I'm laughing at clouds

84
00:11:27,079 --> 00:11:28,449
So dark up above

85
00:11:29,879 --> 00:11:31,439
The sun's in my heart

86
00:11:32,918 --> 00:11:34,718
And I'm ready for love

87
00:11:36,358 --> 00:11:38,588
Let the stormy clouds chase

88
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:41,388
Everyone from the place

89
00:11:43,758 --> 00:11:45,058
Come on with the rain

90
00:11:46,028 --> 00:11:48,127
I've a smile on my face

91
00:11:49,137 --> 00:11:51,197
I'll walk down the lane

92
00:11:52,207 --> 00:11:54,137
With a happy refrain

93
00:11:55,237 --> 00:11:57,107
And I'm singing

94
00:11:57,777 --> 00:11:59,207
Just singing

95
00:12:01,377 --> 00:12:02,536
in the rain

96
00:13:09,312 --> 00:13:10,772
Viddy well, little brother.

97
00:13:11,012 --> 00:13:12,672
Viddy well.

98
00:13:33,031 --> 00:13:36,860
We were all feeling a bit
shagged and fagged and fashed

99
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:41,700
it having been an evening
of some small energy expenditure.

100
00:13:41,970 --> 00:13:46,910
So we got rid of the auto and
stopped at the Korova for a nightcap.

101
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,739
Hello, Lucy.

102
00:13:55,849 --> 00:13:57,549
Had a busy night?

103
00:13:59,259 --> 00:14:01,659
We've been working hard too.

104
00:14:04,059 --> 00:14:05,888
Pardon me, Luce.

105
00:14:13,538 --> 00:14:17,058
There was some sophistos from
the TV studios around the corner

106
00:14:17,338 --> 00:14:19,538
laughing and govoreeting.

107
00:14:19,878 --> 00:14:24,937
The devotchka smeched away, not
caring about the wicked world one bit.

108
00:14:25,847 --> 00:14:29,177
Then the disk on the stereo
twanged off and out.

109
00:14:29,417 --> 00:14:32,717
And in the short silence
before the next one came on

110
00:14:32,957 --> 00:14:36,116
she suddenly came
with a burst of singing.

111
00:14:39,956 --> 00:14:42,296
And it was like, for a moment,
O my brothers

112
00:14:42,596 --> 00:14:45,856
some great bird
had flown into the milk bar.

113
00:14:46,066 --> 00:14:49,296
And I felt all the malenky
little hairs on my plott

114
00:14:49,566 --> 00:14:51,435
standing endwise.

115
00:14:51,875 --> 00:14:55,935
And the shivers crawling up
like slow, malenky lizards

116
00:14:56,205 --> 00:14:57,765
and then down again.

117
00:14:58,045 --> 00:15:00,735
Because I knew what she sang.

118
00:15:00,975 --> 00:15:04,385
It was a bit from
the glorious Ninth, by Ludwig van.

119
00:15:13,224 --> 00:15:15,314
What did you do that for?

120
00:15:15,594 --> 00:15:17,614
For being a bastard
with no manners.

121
00:15:17,924 --> 00:15:22,733
Without a dook of an idea about how
to comport yourself public-wise.

122
00:15:25,003 --> 00:15:27,803
I don't like you should
do what you done.

123
00:15:28,273 --> 00:15:31,673
And I'm not your brother no more
and wouldn't want to be.

124
00:15:35,143 --> 00:15:36,513
Watch that.

125
00:15:37,482 --> 00:15:42,612
Do watch that, if to continue
to be on live thou dost wish.

126
00:15:44,582 --> 00:15:45,852
Yarbles!

127
00:15:46,122 --> 00:15:48,822
Great, bouncy yarblockos to you!

128
00:15:49,292 --> 00:15:52,951
I'll meet you with chain
or nozh or britva anytime.

129
00:15:53,261 --> 00:15:55,851
I'm not having you aiming
tolchocks at me reasonless.

130
00:15:56,331 --> 00:15:59,201
It stands to reason,
I won't have it.

131
00:16:03,971 --> 00:16:07,341
A nozh scrap anytime you say.

132
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:23,949
Doobidoob.

133
00:16:26,189 --> 00:16:28,159
A bit tired maybe.

134
00:16:30,229 --> 00:16:32,129
Best not to say more.

135
00:16:33,469 --> 00:16:35,959
Bedways is rightways now.

136
00:16:36,469 --> 00:16:39,558
So best we go homeways
and get a bit of spatchka.

137
00:16:39,868 --> 00:16:41,338
Right, right?

138
00:16:53,548 --> 00:16:56,247
Where I lived was with
my dada and mum

139
00:16:56,517 --> 00:17:00,927
in municipal flat block
18-A, Linear North.

140
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:28,741
It had been a wonderful evening.

141
00:18:28,971 --> 00:18:32,461
And what I needed now
to give it the perfect ending

142
00:18:32,781 --> 00:18:35,681
was a bit
of the old Ludwig van.

143
00:19:25,798 --> 00:19:27,127
Oh, bliss!

144
00:19:27,697 --> 00:19:29,787
Bliss and heaven!

145
00:19:30,327 --> 00:19:34,857
It was gorgeousness and
gorgeosity made flesh.

146
00:19:35,707 --> 00:19:39,727
It was like a bird
of rarest spun heaven metal.

147
00:19:39,977 --> 00:19:43,406
Or like silvery wine
flowing in a spaceship

148
00:19:43,676 --> 00:19:46,476
gravity all nonsense now.

149
00:19:47,016 --> 00:19:48,416
As I slooshied

150
00:19:48,686 --> 00:19:51,706
I knew such lovely pictures.

151
00:20:11,205 --> 00:20:12,725
Alex. Alex!

152
00:20:19,914 --> 00:20:21,404
What do you want?

153
00:20:21,614 --> 00:20:23,174
It's past eight, Alex.

154
00:20:23,444 --> 00:20:26,504
You don't want to be
late for school, son.

155
00:20:27,954 --> 00:20:30,583
Bit of a pain in the gulliver, Mum.

156
00:20:30,883 --> 00:20:33,383
Leave us be,
and I'll try and sleep it off.

157
00:20:33,623 --> 00:20:36,383
And then I'll be as right
as dodgers for this after.

158
00:20:37,363 --> 00:20:40,423
But you've not been
to school all week, son.

159
00:20:40,693 --> 00:20:41,853
Got to rest, Mum.

160
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,232
Got to get fit.

161
00:20:44,632 --> 00:20:48,122
Otherwise, I'm liable
to miss a lot more school.

162
00:20:48,402 --> 00:20:53,532
I'll put your breakfast in the oven.
I've got to be off meself now.

163
00:20:54,612 --> 00:20:58,812
All right, Mum.
Have a nice day at the factory.

164
00:21:03,151 --> 00:21:06,281
He's not feeling too good
again this morning, Dad.

165
00:21:06,491 --> 00:21:08,391
Yes. Yes, I heard.

166
00:21:08,821 --> 00:21:10,311
You know what time he got in?

167
00:21:10,591 --> 00:21:13,581
No, I don't.
I'd taken me sleepers.

168
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:17,750
I wonder

169
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:22,160
where exactly is it
he goes to work of evenings.

170
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:25,770
Like he says

171
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:28,340
it's mostly odd things he does.

172
00:21:28,610 --> 00:21:29,770
Helping-like

173
00:21:30,009 --> 00:21:32,669
here and there, as it might be.

174
00:22:14,317 --> 00:22:16,306
Hi, hi, hi, Mr. Deltoid.

175
00:22:16,556 --> 00:22:18,486
Funny surprise, seeing you here.

176
00:22:18,726 --> 00:22:22,656
Alex-boy!
Awake at last, yes?

177
00:22:23,296 --> 00:22:26,316
I met your mother
on the way to work, yes?

178
00:22:26,566 --> 00:22:28,556
She gave me the key.

179
00:22:31,365 --> 00:22:33,635
She said something about
a pain somewhere.

180
00:22:33,865 --> 00:22:36,805
Hence, not at school, yes?

181
00:22:37,135 --> 00:22:40,305
A rather intolerable pain
in the head, brother sir.

182
00:22:40,545 --> 00:22:42,665
It should be clear
by this after-lunch.

183
00:22:43,545 --> 00:22:46,135
Or certainly by this evening, yes.

184
00:22:46,415 --> 00:22:49,644
The evening's the great time,
isn't it, Alex-boy?

185
00:22:49,854 --> 00:22:53,374
- Cup of the old chai, sir?
- No time, no time.

186
00:22:53,684 --> 00:22:55,214
Sit, sit, sit!

187
00:22:56,824 --> 00:22:59,584
To what do I owe
this extreme pleasure, sir?

188
00:23:00,324 --> 00:23:01,484
Anything wrong, sir?

189
00:23:01,724 --> 00:23:05,563
Wrong? Why should you
think of anything being wrong?

190
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:08,233
Have you been doing
something you shouldn't?

191
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:09,733
Just a manner of speech.

192
00:23:10,003 --> 00:23:13,033
Yes, well, it's just a manner
of speech from your

193
00:23:13,273 --> 00:23:16,573
post-corrective advisor to you
that you watch out, little Alex.

194
00:23:16,773 --> 00:23:20,332
Because next time it's not
going to be the corrective school.

195
00:23:20,582 --> 00:23:24,912
Next time it'll be the Barley place,
and all my work ruined.

196
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:26,952
If you've no respect
for yourself

197
00:23:27,182 --> 00:23:30,282
you at least might have some
for me, who sweated over you.

198
00:23:30,522 --> 00:23:34,581
A big, black mark, I tell you,
for every one we don't reclaim.

199
00:23:34,861 --> 00:23:38,051
A confession of failure
for every one of you

200
00:23:38,361 --> 00:23:41,231
who ends up in the stripy hole.

201
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,301
I've been doing nothing I shouldn't.

202
00:23:43,601 --> 00:23:46,191
The millicents have nothing
on me, brother.

203
00:23:46,441 --> 00:23:47,771
Sir, I mean.

204
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:50,530
Cut out this clever talk
about millicents.

205
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:53,040
Just because the police
haven't picked you up

206
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:56,440
doesn't mean that you've not
been up to some nastiness.

207
00:23:56,710 --> 00:23:59,260
There was a bit of
nastiness last night.

208
00:23:59,261 --> 00:24:01,810
Some very extreme
nastiness, yes?

209
00:24:02,090 --> 00:24:06,279
A few of a certain Billy-boy's
friends were ambulanced off late.

210
00:24:06,559 --> 00:24:07,919
Your name was mentioned.

211
00:24:08,159 --> 00:24:10,389
The words got to me
by the usual channels.

212
00:24:10,629 --> 00:24:13,459
Certain friends of yours
were named also.

213
00:24:13,759 --> 00:24:16,959
Nobody can prove anything
about anybody, as usual.

214
00:24:17,229 --> 00:24:18,758
I'm warning you, little Alex

215
00:24:19,068 --> 00:24:21,298
being a good friend
to you as always

216
00:24:21,498 --> 00:24:24,298
the one man in this
sore and sick community

217
00:24:24,508 --> 00:24:27,238
who wants to save you
from yourself!

218
00:24:46,627 --> 00:24:48,357
What gets into you all?

219
00:24:48,597 --> 00:24:51,856
We've been studying the problem
for damn well near a century.

220
00:24:52,136 --> 00:24:54,256
But we get no farther
with our studies.

221
00:24:54,536 --> 00:24:57,006
You got a good home here.
Good, loving parents.

222
00:24:57,266 --> 00:24:59,366
You've got not too bad of a brain.

223
00:24:59,676 --> 00:25:02,796
Is it some devil
that crawls inside of you?

224
00:25:03,106 --> 00:25:04,935
Nobody's got anything on me.

225
00:25:05,175 --> 00:25:07,945
I been out of the millicents'
rookers for a long time.

226
00:25:08,175 --> 00:25:12,675
That's just what worries me.
A bit too long to be safe.

227
00:25:12,955 --> 00:25:14,785
You're about due, by my reckoning.

228
00:25:15,015 --> 00:25:16,355
That's why I'm warning you

229
00:25:16,625 --> 00:25:20,054
to keep your handsome
young proboscis out of the dirt.

230
00:25:20,354 --> 00:25:21,684
Do I make myself clear?

231
00:25:21,894 --> 00:25:23,324
As an unmuddied lake, sir.

232
00:25:23,564 --> 00:25:26,964
As clear as an azure sky
of deepest summer.

233
00:25:27,194 --> 00:25:29,494
You can rely on me, sir.

234
00:26:35,630 --> 00:26:37,219
Excuse me, brother.

235
00:26:37,459 --> 00:26:41,089
I ordered this two weeks ago.
Can you see if it's arrived?

236
00:26:42,469 --> 00:26:43,799
Just a minute.

237
00:27:10,097 --> 00:27:11,717
Pardon me, ladies.

238
00:27:20,307 --> 00:27:22,926
Enjoying that, are you, my darling?

239
00:27:25,506 --> 00:27:28,836
A bit cold and pointless,
isn't it, my lovely?

240
00:27:33,246 --> 00:27:36,116
What's happened to yours,
my little sister?

241
00:27:38,285 --> 00:27:39,755
Who you getting, bratty?

242
00:27:39,985 --> 00:27:42,115
Goggly Gogol?
Johnny Zhivago?

243
00:27:42,355 --> 00:27:44,255
The Heaven 17?

244
00:27:48,595 --> 00:27:52,365
What you got back home
to play your fuzzy warbles on?

245
00:27:52,635 --> 00:27:56,864
I bet you've got little
pitiful, portable picnic players.

246
00:27:57,174 --> 00:27:59,294
Come with Uncle
and hear all proper.

247
00:27:59,544 --> 00:28:02,604
Hear angel trumpets
and devil trombones.

248
00:28:02,844 --> 00:28:04,864
You are invited.

249
00:29:27,258 --> 00:29:28,218
Hi, hi, hi, there.

250
00:29:28,458 --> 00:29:29,448
Well, hello.

251
00:29:29,728 --> 00:29:32,348
He are here!
He have arrived!

252
00:29:32,598 --> 00:29:34,188
Hooray!

253
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:37,628
Welly, welly, welly,
welly, welly, welly, well!

254
00:29:39,368 --> 00:29:44,067
To what do I owe the extreme pleasure
of this surprising visit?

255
00:29:49,407 --> 00:29:51,107
We got worried.

256
00:29:53,977 --> 00:29:58,886
There we were, waiting and drinking
away at the old knifey moloko

257
00:29:59,586 --> 00:30:01,646
and you had not turned up.

258
00:30:02,116 --> 00:30:04,316
And we thought
you might have been, like

259
00:30:04,556 --> 00:30:06,886
offended by something
or other.

260
00:30:07,126 --> 00:30:09,556
So around we come to your abode.

261
00:30:14,935 --> 00:30:17,125
Appy polly loggies.

262
00:30:17,435 --> 00:30:20,565
I had something of a pain
in the gulliver, so I had to sleep.

263
00:30:20,835 --> 00:30:23,635
I was not awakened
when I gave orders for wakening.

264
00:30:23,905 --> 00:30:26,305
Sorry about the pain.

265
00:30:27,014 --> 00:30:29,504
Using the gulliver
too much-like, maybe.

266
00:30:32,754 --> 00:30:36,184
Giving orders and
discipline and such, perhaps.

267
00:30:36,684 --> 00:30:38,984
You sure the pain is gone?

268
00:30:39,454 --> 00:30:42,513
You sure you'd not
be happier back in bed?

269
00:31:04,012 --> 00:31:08,312
Let's get things nice
and sparkling clear.

270
00:31:11,682 --> 00:31:14,181
This sarcasm,
if I may call it such

271
00:31:14,391 --> 00:31:17,151
does not become you,
my little brothers.

272
00:31:17,691 --> 00:31:22,131
As I am your droog and leader
I'm entitled to know what goes on.

273
00:31:24,001 --> 00:31:25,191
Now then, Dim.

274
00:31:25,501 --> 00:31:29,630
What does that great big
horsey gape of a grin portend?

275
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:35,370
All right, no more
picking on Dim, brother.

276
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:38,080
That's part of the new way.

277
00:31:45,849 --> 00:31:49,749
New way?
What's this about a new way?

278
00:31:51,059 --> 00:31:55,929
There's been some very large talk
behind my sleeping back, I know it.

279
00:31:57,359 --> 00:32:00,258
If you must have it,
have it, then.

280
00:32:01,068 --> 00:32:03,688
We go around shop crasting
and the like

281
00:32:03,938 --> 00:32:07,528
coming out with a pitiful
rookerfull of money each.

282
00:32:07,868 --> 00:32:10,168
And Will the English
in the coffee mesto

283
00:32:10,408 --> 00:32:13,998
