any malchick tries to crast.

284
00:32:14,248 --> 00:32:16,177
The shiny stuff. The ice!

285
00:32:16,417 --> 00:32:20,437
The big, big money's available,
is what Will the English says.

286
00:32:22,517 --> 00:32:25,787
And what will you do
with the big, big, big money?

287
00:32:26,087 --> 00:32:27,957
Have you not everything you need?

288
00:32:28,257 --> 00:32:31,126
If you need a motorcar,
you pluck it from the trees.

289
00:32:31,426 --> 00:32:34,456
If you need pretty polly,
you take it.

290
00:32:34,696 --> 00:32:39,256
Brother, you think and talk
sometimes like a little child.

291
00:32:40,136 --> 00:32:42,696
Tonight we pull a man-size crast.

292
00:32:44,606 --> 00:32:46,975
Good! Real horror show!

293
00:32:47,205 --> 00:32:49,575
Initiative comes
to thems that wait.

294
00:32:50,245 --> 00:32:53,235
I've taught you much,
my little droogies.

295
00:32:54,645 --> 00:32:58,045
Now tell me what you had in mind,
Georgie-boy.

296
00:33:01,384 --> 00:33:04,584
The old moloko plus first.
Would you not say?

297
00:33:04,824 --> 00:33:08,624
- Something to sharpen us up.
- Some moloko plus.

298
00:33:10,164 --> 00:33:14,994
You got to go there first.
We got a start on you. Moloko Plus!

299
00:33:22,913 --> 00:33:25,343
As we walked along
the flatblock marina

300
00:33:25,643 --> 00:33:29,843
I was calm on the outside,
but thinking all the time.

301
00:33:30,113 --> 00:33:32,642
So now it was to be
Georgie the General

302
00:33:32,952 --> 00:33:35,352
saying what we should do
and what not to do.

303
00:33:35,622 --> 00:33:39,522
And Dim as his mindless,
grinning bulldog.

304
00:33:39,792 --> 00:33:43,422
But suddenly I viddied that
thinking was for the gloopy ones

305
00:33:43,692 --> 00:33:48,821
and that the oomny ones used, like,
inspiration and what Bog sends.

306
00:33:49,331 --> 00:33:53,171
For now it was lovely music
that came to my aid.

307
00:33:53,441 --> 00:33:56,501
There was a window open
with a stereo on

308
00:33:56,771 --> 00:34:00,001
and I viddied right at once
what to do.

309
00:35:05,606 --> 00:35:09,166
I had not cut into any
of Dim's main cables.

310
00:35:09,406 --> 00:35:11,706
And so with the help
of a clean tashtook

311
00:35:11,946 --> 00:35:14,276
the red, red kroovy
soon stopped.

312
00:35:14,546 --> 00:35:18,246
And it did not take long to
quieten the two wounded soldiers

313
00:35:18,445 --> 00:35:21,175
down in the snug
of the Duke of New York.

314
00:35:22,055 --> 00:35:25,575
Now they knew who was
master and leader.

315
00:35:26,095 --> 00:35:28,025
Sheep, thought I.

316
00:35:28,295 --> 00:35:30,455
But a real leader knows
always when, like

317
00:35:30,725 --> 00:35:33,924
to give and show generous
to his unders.

318
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:38,764
Now we're back to where we were.

319
00:35:39,064 --> 00:35:40,364
Yes?

320
00:35:41,204 --> 00:35:43,464
Just like before,
and all forgotten?

321
00:35:43,744 --> 00:35:45,364
Right, right, right?

322
00:35:47,144 --> 00:35:48,274
Right.

323
00:35:51,143 --> 00:35:52,273
Right.

324
00:35:55,753 --> 00:35:56,743
Right.

325
00:35:59,723 --> 00:36:01,883
Well, Georgie-boy

326
00:36:02,223 --> 00:36:06,092
this idea of yours for tonight.
Tell us all about it, then.

327
00:36:07,762 --> 00:36:08,822
Not tonight.

328
00:36:09,132 --> 00:36:10,762
Not this nochy.

329
00:36:11,432 --> 00:36:13,962
Come, come, come, Georgie-boy.

330
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:17,832
You're a big, strong chelloveck,
like us all.

331
00:36:18,102 --> 00:36:21,401
We're not little children,
are we, Georgie-boy?

332
00:36:22,071 --> 00:36:25,741
What, then, didst thou
in thy mind have?

333
00:36:32,581 --> 00:36:34,451
It's this health farm.

334
00:36:35,590 --> 00:36:37,580
A bit out of the town.

335
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:40,080
Isolated.

336
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:45,820
It's owned by this rich ptitsa
who lives there with her cats.

337
00:36:46,430 --> 00:36:50,929
The place is shut down for a week
and she's completely on her own.

338
00:36:52,269 --> 00:36:55,969
It's full up with, like,
gold and silver

339
00:36:56,209 --> 00:36:58,199
and, like, jewels.

340
00:36:59,679 --> 00:37:03,509
Tell me more, Georgie-boy.
Tell me more.

341
00:37:09,218 --> 00:37:10,618
Oh, shit!

342
00:37:29,407 --> 00:37:30,237
Who's there?

343
00:37:30,837 --> 00:37:32,827
Excuse me, can you please help?

344
00:37:33,077 --> 00:37:34,637
There's been a terrible accident!

345
00:37:34,847 --> 00:37:37,816
Can I please use your telephone
for an ambulance?

346
00:37:38,846 --> 00:37:40,816
I'm frightfully sorry.

347
00:37:41,716 --> 00:37:45,246
There's a telephone in the
public house a mile down the road.

348
00:37:45,516 --> 00:37:47,356
I suggest you use that.

349
00:37:47,556 --> 00:37:49,576
But missus, this is an emergency!

350
00:37:49,856 --> 00:37:51,656
It's a matter of life and death!

351
00:37:51,895 --> 00:37:55,655
Me friend's lying in the middle
of the road, bleeding to death!

352
00:37:56,665 --> 00:38:01,655
I'm very sorry, but I never open
the door to strangers after dark.

353
00:38:04,035 --> 00:38:05,835
Very well, madam.

354
00:38:06,205 --> 00:38:08,404
You can't be blamed
for being suspicious

355
00:38:08,674 --> 00:38:12,444
with so many scoundrels
and rogues of the night about.

356
00:38:12,714 --> 00:38:15,274
I'll try and get help
at the pub, then.

357
00:38:15,514 --> 00:38:17,954
I'm sorry if I disturbed you.

358
00:38:18,214 --> 00:38:21,274
Thank you very much.
Good night.

359
00:38:57,921 --> 00:38:59,321
Dim, bend down.

360
00:39:01,661 --> 00:39:04,591
I'll get in that window
and open the front door.

361
00:39:33,189 --> 00:39:34,989
Radlett Police Station?

362
00:39:35,259 --> 00:39:39,159
Good evening. It's Miss Weathers
at Woodmere Health Farm.

363
00:39:41,158 --> 00:39:45,158
I'm sorry to bother you, but
something rather odd just happened.

364
00:39:45,368 --> 00:39:48,268
It's probably nothing at all,
but you never know.

365
00:39:49,168 --> 00:39:52,498
A young man rang the bell,
asking to use the telephone.

366
00:39:52,768 --> 00:39:54,997
He said there's been
some kind of accident.

367
00:39:55,307 --> 00:39:57,707
The thing that caught my
attention was what he said.

368
00:39:57,977 --> 00:40:01,847
His words sounded like those quoted
in the papers this morning

369
00:40:02,117 --> 00:40:06,317
in connection with the writer
and his wife who were assaulted.

370
00:40:07,617 --> 00:40:09,647
Just a few minutes ago.

371
00:40:11,956 --> 00:40:13,686
If you think that's necessary.

372
00:40:13,996 --> 00:40:16,656
But I'm quite sure
he's gone away now.

373
00:40:18,296 --> 00:40:19,996
All right, fine.

374
00:40:20,966 --> 00:40:23,056
Thank you very much.

375
00:40:27,635 --> 00:40:29,235
Hi, hi, hi, there.

376
00:40:29,505 --> 00:40:30,875
At last we meet.

377
00:40:31,075 --> 00:40:35,735
Our brief govorett through the
letter-hole was not satisfactory.

378
00:40:37,045 --> 00:40:38,345
Who are you?

379
00:40:39,545 --> 00:40:41,514
How the hell did you get in here?

380
00:40:43,484 --> 00:40:46,754
What the bloody hell
do you think you're doing?

381
00:40:50,824 --> 00:40:52,594
Naughty, naughty, naughty!

382
00:40:52,864 --> 00:40:55,424
You filthy old soomaka.

383
00:40:55,694 --> 00:40:59,263
Now listen here,
you little bastard!

384
00:40:59,533 --> 00:41:02,993
Just turn round and walk out
of here the same way you came in.

385
00:41:06,203 --> 00:41:07,693
Leave that alone!
Don't touch it!

386
00:41:07,943 --> 00:41:10,373
It's a very important work of art.

387
00:41:21,192 --> 00:41:23,622
What the bloody hell do you want?

388
00:41:24,962 --> 00:41:27,861
To be perfectly honest, madam

389
00:41:28,131 --> 00:41:31,461
I'm taking part in an
international students' contest

390
00:41:31,701 --> 00:41:35,461
to see who can get the most
points for selling magazines.

391
00:41:35,701 --> 00:41:37,791
Cut the shit, sonny

392
00:41:38,071 --> 00:41:42,630
and get out of here before you
get yourself into serious trouble.

393
00:41:42,970 --> 00:41:46,030
I told you to leave that alone!
Now get out of here

394
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:48,140
before I throw you out!

395
00:41:48,610 --> 00:41:51,450
Wretched, slummy bedbug!

396
00:41:52,050 --> 00:41:55,710
I'll teach you to break
into real people's houses.

397
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:57,889
Fucking

398
00:41:58,119 --> 00:41:59,109
little

399
00:41:59,729 --> 00:42:01,219
bastard!

400
00:43:10,855 --> 00:43:13,825
- Let's go. The police are coming!
- One minoota, droogie.

401
00:43:20,534 --> 00:43:23,334
You bastards! I'm blind!

402
00:43:23,574 --> 00:43:27,634
I'm blind, you bastards!
I can't see!

403
00:43:41,523 --> 00:43:44,712
It's no good sitting there in hope,
my little brothers.

404
00:43:44,922 --> 00:43:49,222
I won't say a single solitary
slovo unless I have my lawyer here.

405
00:43:49,562 --> 00:43:52,152
I know the law, you bastards.

406
00:44:00,002 --> 00:44:01,661
Righty-right, Tom.

407
00:44:03,171 --> 00:44:07,041
We'll have to show our friend Alex
here that we know the law too.

408
00:44:07,341 --> 00:44:09,941
But that knowing the law
isn't everything.

409
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,520
Nasty cut you've got there,
little Alex.

410
00:44:28,530 --> 00:44:30,430
Shame, isn't it?

411
00:44:31,299 --> 00:44:33,359
Spoils all your beauty.

412
00:44:35,399 --> 00:44:37,029
Who gave you that, then?

413
00:44:38,469 --> 00:44:40,199
How'd you do that, then?

414
00:44:42,709 --> 00:44:44,769
What's your point, you bastard?

415
00:44:45,049 --> 00:44:47,238
That is for your lady victim.

416
00:44:47,548 --> 00:44:48,738
You ghastly

417
00:44:48,978 --> 00:44:50,708
wretched scoundrel.

418
00:44:53,088 --> 00:44:54,278
Get him off me!

419
00:44:55,258 --> 00:44:57,378
You rotten little bastard!

420
00:45:05,627 --> 00:45:06,897
Good evening, Mr. Deltoid.

421
00:45:07,137 --> 00:45:08,797
Good evening, Sergeant.

422
00:45:09,067 --> 00:45:10,157
They're in room B, sir.

423
00:45:10,437 --> 00:45:12,067
Thank you very much.

424
00:45:13,067 --> 00:45:14,227
Sergeant

425
00:45:14,477 --> 00:45:15,407
Good evening.

426
00:45:15,677 --> 00:45:17,136
Good evening, Inspector.

427
00:45:17,406 --> 00:45:20,306
- Would you like your tea now, sir?
- No, thank you, Sergeant.

428
00:45:20,576 --> 00:45:22,516
May I have some
paper towels, please?

429
00:45:22,816 --> 00:45:25,076
We're interrogating
the prisoner now.

430
00:45:25,286 --> 00:45:28,916
- Perhaps you'd care to come inside.
- Thank you very much.

431
00:45:29,486 --> 00:45:32,455
Good evening, Sergeant.
Good evening, all.

432
00:45:34,455 --> 00:45:37,585
Oh, dear! This boy
does look a mess, doesn't he?

433
00:45:37,825 --> 00:45:39,655
Just look at the state of him.

434
00:45:39,935 --> 00:45:41,865
Love's young nightmare-like.

435
00:45:42,135 --> 00:45:44,035
Violence makes violence.

436
00:45:44,305 --> 00:45:46,295
He resisted his lawful arrestors.

437
00:45:47,834 --> 00:45:51,104
This is the end of the line for me.

438
00:45:51,304 --> 00:45:54,474
The end of the line, yes.

439
00:45:54,844 --> 00:45:56,314
And what of me, brother sir?

440
00:45:56,514 --> 00:45:58,204
Speak up for me.
I'm not so bad.

441
00:45:58,484 --> 00:46:00,474
I was led on by
the treachery of others.

442
00:46:00,714 --> 00:46:03,613
Sings the roof off lovely,
he does, sir.

443
00:46:03,853 --> 00:46:07,113
Where are my treacherous droogs?
Get them before they get away!

444
00:46:07,353 --> 00:46:09,183
It was all their idea, brothers.

445
00:46:09,453 --> 00:46:12,123
They forced me to do it.
I'm innocent!

446
00:46:18,862 --> 00:46:21,562
You are now a murderer,
little Alex.

447
00:46:22,302 --> 00:46:23,562
A murderer.

448
00:46:24,402 --> 00:46:26,392
Not true, sir.

449
00:46:26,642 --> 00:46:28,472
It was only a slight tolchok.

450
00:46:28,672 --> 00:46:31,202
She were breathing, I swear it.

451
00:46:31,682 --> 00:46:33,871
I've just come from the hospital.

452
00:46:34,151 --> 00:46:36,411
Your victim has died.

453
00:46:36,681 --> 00:46:39,841
You try to frighten me.
Admit so, sir.

454
00:46:40,091 --> 00:46:42,051
This is some new form of torture.

455
00:46:42,321 --> 00:46:45,591
- Say it, brother sir.
- It'll be your own torture.

456
00:46:45,861 --> 00:46:49,660
I hope to God
it'll torture you to madness.

457
00:46:51,500 --> 00:46:54,590
If you'd care to give him a bash
in the chops, don't mind us.

458
00:46:54,830 --> 00:46:56,600
We'll hold him down.

459
00:46:57,340 --> 00:47:00,530
He must be a great
disappointment to you, sir.

460
00:47:29,968 --> 00:47:33,628
This is the real weepy and tragic
part of the story beginning

461
00:47:33,908 --> 00:47:36,097
O my brothers and only friends.

462
00:47:36,407 --> 00:47:38,807
After a trial,
with judges and a jury

463
00:47:39,077 --> 00:47:43,307
