02:06:52,097 --> 02:06:54,797
"You can do whatever
you like with these"

1530
02:06:56,397 --> 02:06:58,197
Eggiwegs.

1531
02:06:58,737 --> 02:07:00,667
I would like

1532
02:07:00,907 --> 02:07:02,237
to smash them.

1533
02:07:03,037 --> 02:07:04,337
And pick them all up

1534
02:07:04,547 --> 02:07:06,207
and throw

1535
02:07:06,447 --> 02:07:07,876
Fucking hell!

1536
02:07:08,746 --> 02:07:11,076
There. That's all there is to it.

1537
02:07:11,746 --> 02:07:13,236
Are you all right?

1538
02:07:14,116 --> 02:07:15,516
Hope so.

1539
02:07:15,686 --> 02:07:18,716
Is that the end, then?
I was quite enjoying that.

1540
02:07:19,026 --> 02:07:20,316
Good. I'm glad.

1541
02:07:20,626 --> 02:07:21,716
How many did I get right?

1542
02:07:22,025 --> 02:07:23,785
It's not that kind of a test.

1543
02:07:24,065 --> 02:07:27,355
But you seem well on the way
to making a complete recovery.

1544
02:07:28,035 --> 02:07:29,395
When do I get out, then?

1545
02:07:29,665 --> 02:07:32,295
I'm sure it won't be long now.

1546
02:07:33,675 --> 02:07:35,225
So I waited

1547
02:07:35,535 --> 02:07:37,005
and, O my brothers

1548
02:07:37,444 --> 02:07:38,804
I got a lot better

1549
02:07:39,044 --> 02:07:42,304
munching away at eggiwegs
and lomticks of toast

1550
02:07:42,544 --> 02:07:45,014
and lovely steakie-wakes.

1551
02:07:45,214 --> 02:07:46,704
And then one day

1552
02:07:46,984 --> 02:07:51,074
they said I was going to have
a very special visitor.

1553
02:07:56,523 --> 02:07:59,223
Just wait outside for a moment,
would you, Officer?

1554
02:08:02,333 --> 02:08:04,493
I'm afraid my change of schedule
has thrown you.

1555
02:08:04,763 --> 02:08:06,993
The patient's in the middle
of supper.

1556
02:08:07,233 --> 02:08:10,072
That's quite all right, Minister.
No trouble at all.

1557
02:08:11,542 --> 02:08:14,532
- Good evening, my boy.
- Hi there, my little droogies.

1558
02:08:14,772 --> 02:08:16,572
How are you getting on, young man?

1559
02:08:16,942 --> 02:08:19,172
Great, sir. Just great.

1560
02:08:19,942 --> 02:08:21,542
Can I do anything more for you?

1561
02:08:21,752 --> 02:08:23,541
I don't think so, Sir Leslie.

1562
02:08:23,751 --> 02:08:26,411
Then I leave you to it.
Nurse!

1563
02:08:29,251 --> 02:08:32,521
You seem to have a whole ward
to yourself, my boy.

1564
02:08:32,791 --> 02:08:34,021
Yes, sir.

1565
02:08:34,591 --> 02:08:36,961
And a very lonely place
it is too

1566
02:08:37,201 --> 02:08:39,560
when I wake up in the night
with me pain.

1567
02:08:41,030 --> 02:08:43,260
Anyway, good to see you
on the mend.

1568
02:08:43,540 --> 02:08:46,130
I kept in touch
with the hospital, of course.

1569
02:08:46,400 --> 02:08:48,200
And now I've come down
personally

1570
02:08:48,440 --> 02:08:50,030
to see how you're getting along.

1571
02:08:50,480 --> 02:08:52,770
I've suffered the tortures
of the damned.

1572
02:08:52,980 --> 02:08:54,469
Tortures of the damned.

1573
02:08:54,779 --> 02:08:57,809
Yes, I can appreciate that
you've had an extremely

1574
02:08:58,049 --> 02:09:00,809
Oh, look. Let me help you
with that, shall I?

1575
02:09:03,049 --> 02:09:07,249
I can tell you that I, and the
government of which I'm a member

1576
02:09:07,489 --> 02:09:11,448
are deeply sorry about this,
my boy. Deeply sorry.

1577
02:09:11,658 --> 02:09:12,928
We tried to help you.

1578
02:09:13,158 --> 02:09:17,258
We followed recommendations
that turned out to be wrong.

1579
02:09:17,668 --> 02:09:21,498
An inquiry will place the
responsibility where it belongs.

1580
02:09:22,168 --> 02:09:25,397
We want you to regard us
as friends.

1581
02:09:25,637 --> 02:09:26,907
We put you right.

1582
02:09:27,307 --> 02:09:29,247
You're getting
the best of treatment.

1583
02:09:29,447 --> 02:09:31,677
We never wished you harm.

1584
02:09:31,977 --> 02:09:34,647
But there are some who did, and do.

1585
02:09:35,147 --> 02:09:37,817
And I think you know who those are.

1586
02:09:38,417 --> 02:09:42,186
There are certain people who wanted
to use you for political ends.

1587
02:09:42,456 --> 02:09:44,826
They would have been
glad to have you dead

1588
02:09:45,026 --> 02:09:48,186
for they thought they could then
blame it on the government.

1589
02:09:48,826 --> 02:09:51,166
There is also a certain man

1590
02:09:51,366 --> 02:09:53,856
a writer of subversive
literature

1591
02:09:54,166 --> 02:09:56,265
who has been howling
for your blood.

1592
02:09:56,465 --> 02:09:59,875
He's been mad with desire
to stick a knife into you.

1593
02:10:00,345 --> 02:10:01,835
But you're safe from him now.

1594
02:10:02,105 --> 02:10:04,135
We put him away.

1595
02:10:06,045 --> 02:10:09,135
He found out that you
had done wrong to him.

1596
02:10:09,715 --> 02:10:12,114
At least he believed
you had done wrong.

1597
02:10:12,384 --> 02:10:16,614
He formed this idea in his head
that you had been responsible

1598
02:10:16,894 --> 02:10:20,324
for the death of someone
near and dear to him.

1599
02:10:21,164 --> 02:10:22,284
He was a menace.

1600
02:10:22,494 --> 02:10:24,624
We put him away
for his own protection.

1601
02:10:24,834 --> 02:10:26,193
And also for yours.

1602
02:10:26,963 --> 02:10:28,333
Where is he now?

1603
02:10:28,563 --> 02:10:32,023
We put him away
where he can do you no harm.

1604
02:10:32,303 --> 02:10:35,363
You see, we are looking
after your interests.

1605
02:10:35,673 --> 02:10:37,703
We are interested in you.

1606
02:10:38,473 --> 02:10:41,532
When you leave, you'll have no
worries. We'll see to everything.

1607
02:10:41,782 --> 02:10:43,902
A good job on a good salary.

1608
02:10:44,152 --> 02:10:45,872
What job and how much?

1609
02:10:46,752 --> 02:10:50,712
You'll have an interesting job at
a salary you regard as adequate.

1610
02:10:50,952 --> 02:10:53,152
Not only for the job
you're going to do

1611
02:10:53,422 --> 02:10:57,051
and in compensation for what
you believe you have suffered

1612
02:10:57,291 --> 02:11:00,961
but also because
you are helping us.

1613
02:11:02,161 --> 02:11:03,761
Helping you?

1614
02:11:04,001 --> 02:11:07,161
We always help our friends,
don't we?

1615
02:11:13,680 --> 02:11:15,910
It is no secret
that this government

1616
02:11:16,140 --> 02:11:19,310
has lost a lot of popularity
because of you, my boy.

1617
02:11:19,580 --> 02:11:22,980
There are some who think that at
the next election we shall be out.

1618
02:11:23,180 --> 02:11:25,950
The press has chosen to take
a very unfavorable view

1619
02:11:26,150 --> 02:11:27,589
of what we tried to do.

1620
02:11:28,519 --> 02:11:31,819
But public opinion
has a way of changing.

1621
02:11:32,089 --> 02:11:33,789
And you, Alex

1622
02:11:34,029 --> 02:11:35,859
if I may call you Alex.

1623
02:11:36,129 --> 02:11:39,429
Certainly.
What do they call you at home?

1624
02:11:40,769 --> 02:11:42,029
My name is Frederick.

1625
02:11:42,998 --> 02:11:44,838
As I was saying, Alex

1626
02:11:45,108 --> 02:11:50,008
you can be instrumental
in changing the public's verdict.

1627
02:11:53,308 --> 02:11:55,338
Do you understand, Alex?

1628
02:11:56,218 --> 02:11:58,477
Do I make myself clear?

1629
02:12:01,387 --> 02:12:03,687
As an unmuddied lake, Fred.

1630
02:12:04,227 --> 02:12:07,627
As clear as an azure sky
of deepest summer.

1631
02:12:07,857 --> 02:12:09,297
You can rely on me, Fred.

1632
02:12:09,527 --> 02:12:10,857
Good.

1633
02:12:11,127 --> 02:12:12,567
Good boy.

1634
02:12:13,636 --> 02:12:15,466
I understand you're fond of music.

1635
02:12:15,736 --> 02:12:17,896
I have arranged a little
surprise for you.

1636
02:12:18,206 --> 02:12:19,636
Surprise?

1637
02:12:19,866 --> 02:12:21,566
One that I hope
that you will like

1638
02:12:21,836 --> 02:12:23,236
as a

1639
02:12:24,046 --> 02:12:25,406
how shall we put it

1640
02:12:25,646 --> 02:12:28,875
as a symbol of
our new understanding.

1641
02:12:29,875 --> 02:12:33,175
An understanding
between two friends.

1642
02:13:53,220 --> 02:13:55,850
was cured, all right!
